Step 1: Identify the quick (or liquid) assets. These typically include:
• Cash on Hand = 627601.28  
• Bank Deposits = -129032.26  
• Interest Receivable = 13240.11  
• Accounts Receivable = 15362611.64  

Step 2: Sum these quick assets.
• Sum = 627601.28 + (-129032.26) + 13240.11 + 15362611.64  
• First, 627601.28 - 129032.26 = 498569.02  
• Then, 498569.02 + 13240.11 = 511809.13  
• Finally, 511809.13 + 15362611.64 = 15874420.77  

Step 3: Identify the Current Liabilities.
• Total Current Liabilities = 3143833.89  

Step 4: Calculate the Quick Ratio.
• Quick Ratio = Quick Assets / Current Liabilities = 15874420.77 / 3143833.89  
• This calculates to approximately 5.05  

Thus, the answer is:
